## 5. Workflow / Process Flow

### Step-by-Step: From Attack Detection to Alert Generation

```
 STEP 1: DATA COLLECTION
 ┌──────────────────────────────┐
 │ Collectors gather data:       │
 │ • System metrics (psutil)     │
 │ • Network packets (scapy)     │
 │ • Windows Event Logs          │
 │ • File system changes         │
 └──────────┬───────────────────┘
            │ publish("system_event")
            ▼
 STEP 2: DETECTION
 ┌──────────────────────────────┐
 │ Rules Engine checks:          │
 │ • CPU > 85%? → Alert          │
 │ • Memory > 90%? → Alert       │
 │ • Cooldown: 30 sec            │
 │                               │
 │ Traffic Model (IsolationForest):  │
 │ • Extract features [size,     │
 │   port, proto, hour]          │
 │ • predict() → anomaly?        │
 │ • Retrain every 100 packets   │
 └──────────┬───────────────────┘
            │ publish("alert")
            ▼
 STEP 3: AI ANALYSIS
 ┌──────────────────────────────┐
 │ 3a. Keyword Scoring:          │
 │   "mimikatz" → 90 points      │
 │   "nmap" → 60 points          │
 │                               │
 │ 3b. LLM Analysis (Ollama):    │
 │   Prompt: "Act as L3 Analyst. │
 │   Is this a false positive    │
 │   or real attack?"            │
 │                               │
 │ 3c. Risk Scoring:             │
 │   severity → risk score       │
 │   accumulate per host         │
 │                               │
 │ 3d. Hunter AI:                │
 │   Hypothesis → Evidence →     │
 │   Verdict (MALICIOUS/BENIGN)  │
 └──────────┬───────────────────┘
            │ publish("alert") with enrichment
            ▼
 STEP 4: PREDICTIVE ANALYSIS
 ┌──────────────────────────────┐
 │ Map alert → MITRE TTP:        │
 │   "mimikatz" → T1003          │
 │                               │
 │ Walk MITRE attack graph:      │
 │   T1003 → T1021 (90%!)       │
 │   "Attacker likely to attempt │
 │    Lateral Movement next"     │
 └──────────┬───────────────────┘
            │ publish("alert", type="Prediction")
            ▼
 STEP 5: SOAR RESPONSE
 ┌──────────────────────────────┐
 │ Decision Matrix:              │
 │ • Whitelisted? → Ignore       │
 │ • Threat Score > 50? → BLOCK  │
 │ • Otherwise → AI Analyst      │
 │                               │
 │ Active Defense:               │
 │ • block_ip() via netsh/       │
 │   iptables                    │
 │ • Discord notification        │
 │ • Incident auto-creation      │
 └──────────┬───────────────────┘
            │ publish("firewall_event")
            ▼
 STEP 6: LOGGING & DISPLAY
 ┌──────────────────────────────┐
 │ SIEM: Blockchain log entry    │
 │   hash = SHA256(id + time +   │
 │          prev_hash + msg)     │
 │                               │
 │ WebSocket → UI Dashboard      │
 │ Redis → Cross-service sync    │
 │ Incident Manager → DB record  │
 └──────────────────────────────┘
```

