## 7. Technology Stack

| Category | Technology | Purpose |
|:---|:---|:---|
| **Backend** | Python 3.10+ | Core language for all services |
| **API Framework** | FastAPI + Uvicorn | REST API with async I/O, auto-docs (Swagger) |
| **Real-time** | WebSockets (`websockets` lib) | Agent telemetry + UI streaming |
| **Frontend** | React + TypeScript + Vite | Dashboard SPA |
| **UI Library** | TailwindCSS + Shadcn/UI | Modern, responsive design |
| **ML** | scikit-learn (Isolation Forest) | Network traffic anomaly detection |
| **LLM** | Ollama (Llama3) | Natural-language threat analysis |
| **Graph Analysis** | NetworkX | MITRE ATT&CK kill-chain modeling |
| **Packet Inspection** | Scapy | Deep Packet Inspection (DPI) |
| **System Monitoring** | psutil | CPU, RAM, Disk, Process metrics |
| **File Monitoring** | watchdog | File Integrity Monitoring (FIM) |
| **Authentication** | python-jose (JWT) + passlib (bcrypt) | Token-based auth with RBAC |
| **Database (SIEM)** | SQLite | Blockchain-secured log storage |
| **Database (Metrics)** | TimescaleDB (PostgreSQL) | Time-series storage |
| **Message Bus** | Redis (Pub/Sub) | Cross-service event distribution |
| **Containerization** | Docker + Docker Compose | Service orchestration |
| **Networking** | [netsh](file:///d:/project/Sentinel/Sentinel_level8/Sentinel_Level8_Enterprise%20-%20Copy/c2_core/core/firewall.py#243-260) / `iptables` | OS-level firewall enforcement |
| **Windows APIs** | pywin32 | Event Log collection |
| **Notifications** | Discord Webhooks | Real-time alert notifications |
| **Threat Intel** | AbuseIPDB API | IP reputation lookup |

### Why These Technologies Were Chosen

- **FastAPI over Flask/Django**: Native async support, automatic OpenAPI docs, high performance (~15k req/sec). Perfect for security workloads needing non-blocking I/O.
- **SQLite over PostgreSQL for SIEM**: Zero configuration, file-based, embedded. Ideal for rapid prototyping and demonstration. TimescaleDB is added for production-grade time-series needs.
- **Isolation Forest**: Unsupervised ML — no labeled data needed. Works well for anomaly detection with unknown attack patterns.
- **Ollama (Llama3)**: Local LLM inference — no data leaves the network (privacy). No cloud API costs.
- **Redis**: Ultra-fast Pub/Sub for real-time event distribution between microservices. Sub-millisecond latency.
- **Docker**: Ensures consistent deployment across environments. Each service is independently scalable.
- **React + TypeScript**: Type safety, component reusability, and the richest ecosystem for building enterprise dashboards.

